  "text": "In this the conundrum highlighted to us by educators concerns offering simulation to cohorts with a very broad range of prior clinical experience, coupled with significant variation in cultural background (for a full description, see [CITATION_1] . This complexity is intensified because the sequencing of simulation in relation to clinical placements within the overall degree is not uniform. Some students have just returned from placements, others are about to do theirs. What emerges in our discussion are issues relating to taking on unfamiliar roles; and managing what is attended to or not in the simulation.",
